algorithm.text.t1: Data source component, supports accessing data from relational data sources, supoOS instances, file data sources, api data sources, and also supports extracting data via SQL.
algorithm.text.t2: Supports reading data via Kafka and RocketMQ from message queues and mapping message data into a virtual "two-dimensional table" for downstream operator processing.
algorithm.text.t3: Support selecting tables and views on ODS and DW.
algorithm.text.t4: Exporting processed data to relational data sources, supOS instances, file data sources, api data sources.
algorithm.text.t5: Supports sending processed data to a message queue, such as KAFKA, MQTT, RocketMQ.
algorithm.text.t6: Supports for exporting data to DW (DWD tables and DIM tables).
algorithm.text.t7: Exports the processed data to habse data source.
algorithm.text.t8: Supports data quality detection. Detect data according to certain policies, and perform operations to error data such as discard, ignore and repair.
algorithm.text.t9: Implements CRUD operations on relational data sources via SQL commands.
algorithm.text.t10: Redefines data structure by modifying data field name and description.
algorithm.text.t11: Set filter conditions on several data fields, support fields filtered by constants and variables, similar to where conditions in a database.
algorithm.text.t12: Join multiple database tables using inline, left, right, and full joins, and support joins across source databases.
algorithm.text.t13: Supports sorting specified fields in ASC or DESC order. If multiple fields are specified for sorting, they are prioritized in order of precedence.
algorithm.text.t14: Supports merging data from multiple tables by column to form a new table.
algorithm.text.t15: Supports filling null values and empty strings in data with maximum, minimum, average, constant, variable, fit, and custom formulas.
algorithm.text.t16: Supports conversion of numeric, boolean, character and date types to each other, as well as string processing, character replacement, data replacement and field processing.
algorithm.text.t17: Complements temporal discontinuities to obtain continuous, complete data and reduce the difficulty of subsequent data processing.
algorithm.text.t18: Reassigns values to initialized variables, mainly used in data incremental synchronization scenarios
algorithm.text.t19: Supports various aggregation operations on data, including summation, maximum, minimum and average values
algorithm.text.t20: Supports table transposition of relational data sources and file data, I.E. Changing the horizontal and vertical orientation of the table, and outputting the processed data results only to a file.
algorithm.text.t21: Custom extraction and analysis of data sources by writing scripts, making data processing more flexible.
algorithm.text.t22: Supports programming x-bd algorithm models in tasks, access to external data as a source of data for model operations, and supports outputting model operation results to various data sources including object models.
algorithm.text.t23: Provides online update service for x-bd algorithm model
algorithm.text.t24: Generates sample set data and syncs to x-bd sample set management.
algorithm.text.t25: Operators in the branching task filter and triage the data to up to 5 downstream operators based on the set branch condition expressions, where the condition expressions can be generated by functions, variables, and fields to process the data differently based on different data characteristics.
algorithm.text.t26: Desensitizes several fields by data fuzzing. Supports selecting the starting position and length of the desensitized fields, the desensitized data will overwrite original data and flow to downstream operator.
